Political & Philosophical Compass

Answer 25 questions to explore your political and philosophical positions

Please answer all questions before submitting.
POLITICAL FOUNDATIONS (1-10)
1. The United States is a net positive for the global population.
2. Lobbying should be banned from politics.
3. Deporting immigrants is sometimes necessary and moral.
4. One should prioritize their nation above all.
5. One should prioritize their race/ethnicity above all.
6. A nation's moral foundation requires religious belief.
7. Countries should prioritize international relationships and trade.
8. Military intervention in other countries is sometimes necessary to protect national interests.
9. Rich countries owe reparations to countries they colonized or exploited.
10. Gun ownership is a fundamental right that shouldn't be restricted.
PHILOSOPHY & VALUES (11-17)
11. The meaning of life must be created by individuals, not inherited from tradition or religion.
12. You control which thoughts you act on, but not the thoughts themselves.
13. Some people are incapable of self-governance and need to be managed by others.
14. Tradition and community are more important than self-expression.
15. A person's worth is determined by what they contribute, not by their existence.
16. Intuition reveals truths that logic cannot reach.
17. Suffering purifies and strengthens the soul.
ECONOMICS & LABOR (18-22)
18. Most human misery comes from material conditions, not personal choices.
19. Workers should collectively own and control the companies they work for.
20. The wealthy earned their money and deserve to keep it.
21. Nationalizing major industries would benefit society.
22. Under socialism, people would still need incentives to work hard.
SOCIAL & CONTEMPORARY (23-25)
23. Gender roles are mostly biological, not socially constructed.
24. Police forces should be significantly reduced or abolished.
25. Economic growth should be prioritized over environmental protection.
